            "body": "> With all that said, my preference would be to just leave things as they are, but I appreciate the arguments for doing this and hopefully the perf loss is negligible.\r\n\r\nI second this; it feels premature to take a wrench to API names when the API itself is still under heavy (re)construction. There's no guarantee that we won't have to introduce an `nvim_get_option2` later if we do this now. Much better to look at the final state and make a holistic decision.",
