            "body": "> Maybe we could rename `nvim_set_option_value` to just `nvim_set_option`?\r\n\r\nor `nvim_option_set`, yes.\r\n\r\n> it feels premature to take a wrench to API names when the API itself is still under heavy (re)construction.\r\n\r\nMy motivation is to get this done before 0.10 release. If the function takes `opts` and returns `Dict`, it's future-proof. So this is just about naming (and avoiding _proliferation_ of clumsy names like `foo_info` and `foo_value`, though I am also working on automation to enforce naming conventions).",
