        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Just to note, one way to avoid the dictionary allocation is to add a lstate argument to the function, and if present, build the table directly onto the Lua stack and avoid the arena middle-man.\r\n\r\n> We did this for nvim_buf_get_lines and it resulted in a 30% gain in performance. Not magnitudes, but still worth doing.\r\n\r\nThis was over the old status quo of using _nested allocations_ and xfree panic, not compared to the arena pattern. Especially with Dictionaries the overhead of the Arena is much lower, as static key names can just be used as such, and are not copied to the arena. Though as a newer complement using typed `dict(foo)` retvals work now for direct lua table construction without needing `lstate` special casing (which still will be worth it in some micro-optimization cases, but for anything regarding options I suspect arena/keydict will be good enough).",
            "created_at": "2024-02-13T11:01:15Z",
